column8: Smoov is the first platform built to help couples automatically split and manage their shared expenses, before they have a shared bank account. Millions of couples are sending money back and forth every single day and money is the number one reason relationships fail. Today the process for splitting bills and expenses is manual, time consuming, and can be awkward or tense, plus no one likes doing math. Smoov makes it automatic, accurate and easy. While mirroring consumer behavior of sending money to each other via mobile. How? Smoov integrates with users' existing credit and debit cards and pulls transactions into a private running list.  This creates a very low barrier to entry and eliminates awkward conversations about signing up for a new card together - plus they don't want to do that anyway. Couples set up a default split % for all of their shared expenses that they can adjust on a per transaction basis if they want.  Users swipe which expenses they want to move from their private view to the couples shared view.  Smoov keeps track of the total damage (who owes who how much) and whenever the couple is ready, they can settle up via direct ACH transfer through Smoov. Why? Modern couples who value their financial autonomy are getting married later in life, with more independent wealth and studies show they are fully merging their respective finances less and less - in a world where timing is everything, Smoov fits perfectly into that macro trend among others.

It provides embedded finance services allowing clients to open digital wallets for their users and to manage them using application programming interface (API) integration. As a BaaS provider, Whillet handles all licensing requirements, relieving the client of that responsibility. This includes websites, apps, marketplaces and other platforms set up for client users, facilitating such things as bank accounts, electronic money accounts and bonus accounts.   Customer wallets can be accessed in a variety of ways, such as via a mobile app or through a website. The embedded finance technology allows clients to substantially increase revenue and improve unit economy indicators.   A good example of how Whillet works is by employing multilevel processing solutions for loyalty programs while, simultaneously, partners get easy management of customized loyalty programs, thereby rewarding regular users with bonuses and real money which they can spend on further purchases.   Multi-billing facilities enable payments to be distributed among all participants in the sales process - the customer, suppliers, store (or site), couriers, and so on. This automated system saves companies time for pursuing more important strategic tasks.   A branded, customized wallet can include any methods of depositing and withdrawing money that the customer chooses. Debit and credit cards, mobile payments, e-money, transfer money providers, and so on. All of the above will be provided as an integrated link in the customer's account. Whillet's prime focus is on the B2B and B2C markets. The company works with marketplaces, sharing platforms, retail chains of various sizes, car dealerships, insurance and travel companies, postal service providers, contractor-user and production-delivery-customer models, car parkings, fines payments, license acquisitions, online stores, freelance exchanges, taxi companies, and gas stations - the list of possible uses just goes on and on.   Whillet, based in Palo Alto, California, has a highly professional team with experience of serving more than 2000 partners worldwide - that’s over 30 million open wallets and more than 10 million transactions carried out each and every day.

column8: Dapple Pay is a 21st Century Mobile "Banking" Platform that aims to eliminate oppressively high banking fees and retail "cashless" discrimination by allowing users to use their Smart Phones as their primary banking source, rather than their "classic" bank. As their brainstorming expanded, these former financial services professionals reexamined the available mobile wallets and payment systems and realized that the over 25% of unbanked and underbanked americans, mostly Minorities and Immigrants, needed relief too. Dapple Pay Wallet was born. Upon launch, Dapple Pay will be available in iOS and Android devices. Dapple Pay can be used internationally, and where contactless (NFC) payment consoles are used. Once your data is developed, it constructs machine or deep learning models optimized to the highest accuracy to process your data. You can make changes to the output through some Calibration code or leave just leave it to Hazlo. Finally, your model is deployed and now you can use it anywhere: websites, apps, or your system backend — it's all game.

NFTMe believes Real People are Non-Fungible and beautiful.  To that end we’re building a NFT platform that enables Influencers to NFT themselves in a high quality 360 4K HD resolution Avatar.  We’re an Art first focused company that believes each “Moment” NFT’d in our studios must be of artwork quality.  Our NFTs will be composable which enables a vibrant Creator Community to modify the models using beautiful environmental and background changes. Each newly composable NFT will provide creators opportunities to re-mint the underlying smart contract for creator resale commissions. Based on our community feedback we’re building a play to earn game that uses the customized NFTs and building Metaverse bridges to enable interoperability of our avatars.

Welcome to Sal's Pizzeria. Our restaurant was founded by Sal's son-in-law, Matthew Darienzo, out of his love and respect for both Sal and the traditional pizza he makes. Sal's Pizzeria is excited to bring the best pizza in Mission Viejo, California to pizza lovers in Orange County. Our pizza is made with authentic NY style, and we're proud to offer Grandma Pie pizza and Sicilian pizza (thick crust). In addition to pizza, we also have garlic knots, sandwiches, salads, pastas, calzones, desserts and more. Our goal is to provide our customers with a great pizza experience, and we're committed to offering the best possible product and service. Thanks for choosing Sal's Pizzeria! Sal (born in Sicily, Italy) came to America as a young man and eventually settled in Brooklyn, New York. It was there that he met and married Matthew's mother-in-law. They started a family and Sal began working in pizzerias to support them. He quickly developed a reputation for making the best pizzas around. When Matthew expressed an interest in opening his own pizzeria, Sal taught him everything he knew. Now, we carry on Sal's legacy by serving up delicious Sicilian. Looking for the best pizza in Mission Viejo, CA? Look no further than Sal's Pizzeria! We offer authentic NY Pizza, and Grandma Pie pizza, Sicilian pizza (thick crust) and Italian food favorites like garlic knots, sandwiches, salads, pastas, calzones, desserts and more. Our pizzas are made with the freshest ingredients and our dough is made fresh daily. Come try our famous thin crust pizza or our new gluten free pizza today! We guarantee you'll be back for more!
